<br>
1. Get maximum mana regen.  Horse, bard, c5, MC3, mod rod, both harvest, FT15, if possible lunar whispers(self only buff), Force shield, SD, necros. <br>
<br>
2. Have a deep manapool.<br>
<br>
3. When mob is nearly dead, you should have enough mana left to do a full burn or pretty close to it.  <br>
<br>
Landing a 9492 burn when a mob is under 6% health helps considerably.  Especially if half the raid is dead.  If its that close there is a chance one or more tanks is dead as well as a good amount of clerics.  <br>
<br>
As a wizard who has just nuked the whole fight, your pretty close to crossing over the aggro line.  You can get summoned at anytime but you know your sitting on all this mana and a little bit more damage is going to kill this mob.<br>
<br>
This is where manaburn has its place.  Is it situational? absolutly.  Is it for every wizard? no, get your other AA's in order first.  Don't even think about manaburn until you have over 160AA.  It does have its place though and can be helpful although not used regularly.<br>
<br>
Its nowhere near what it was before, I think they should either remove the cap or remove the 1 min timer.  Both in place really hurts the number of ways it can be used. <p><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;font-size:medium;"><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">Valas Defai</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.insidiousblood.net/"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-size:x-small;">A member of Insidious Blood</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=211027&amp;resize=true" target="top"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;font-size:xx-small;">My Magelo</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wandork>Wandor K</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>Warriors ph34r me!<BR>Gnomercy for Gno-one!</span><br>  Posts: 2164<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/3/03 12:47 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mana burn</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I see lots of people questioning Wandor's stated strat for finishing off the mezzable RC's... willing to bet you haven't fought them.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
That would be my guess.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>24k in 6 minutes?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
No, not 24k in 6 minutes. When the first councilman dies, you have 6 minutes to kill the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>11 OTHER COUNCIL MEN.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Bare minimum you are going to have 6 mezzed councilmen. With some of the regen they get from being mezzed for the better part of 3 hours, you have somewhere around 250-300k damage that needs to be done in what ever time you have left after killing the first 6 councilmen - usually around 3-3.5 minutes left on timer. So yes, DPS is at a premium. When you have 6 mezzed 3k hitters that have a 1k+DoT AE, they need to die fast.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>HAHA, like you are going to waste your entire manabar on something like 1 of the 6 councilmen. That takes you out of the fight all together.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
When you have 6+ wizards to MB they die fast enough that you can med up so you have mana to cast on the Avatar of Earth. As long as you beat the timer, who cares how much mana you have? With 1 MB per mob, there is hardly enough time to cast a 2nd nuke. The AoE is a puss and it's easy to kite him around a couple minutes while you rez and rebuff. If you don't beat the timer, grats on wasting 3+ hours of your guilds time. Personally, I would rather not take the chance of running out of time because yor DPS drops too much when people start falling to 6 AEs in a short time.<br>
<br>
Besides, I don't know about you, but on a raid I have well over 100 mana/tick regen so by the time the AoE hits camp, I have plenty of mana to nuke at will. It doesn't take a genius to save Harvest of Druzzil and a mod rod click to get a little bump to get a little mana going. Last time we killed the Rathe, I MB'd the 2nd mezzed councilman. By the time the AoE got to us I was at 60% mana so I had more than enough to chain nuke until he died. I hardly consider that being out of the fight. <p><div align="center" class="font-size: 11px; font-family: arial">
